entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how close are you to them

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: really close

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is great who is someone that is been a positive influence in your life

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: my meditation teacher

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: can you tell me about that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah i i used to be very shy and self conscious and had a lot of anxiety and i would worry a lot about the future and i took classes in meditation and yoga classes and it really helped me to be more confident and more relaxed and just enjoy life a lot more

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good what do you do to relax

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: meditate and do yoga

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are some things that make you really mad

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: let is see really mad i guess i do not know about mad i do not get mad that often but frustrated i would say like being stuck in traffic or people that do mean things to other people for no real reason

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what do you do when you are annoyed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i usually if it is i usually talk to somebody about it if i can or if i can not then i will usually do meditation or yoga and try and just let it go

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good how are you at controlling your temper

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: pretty good at controlling my temper

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: when was the last time you argued with someone and what was it about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: with my girlfriend and it was about she was driving on the freeway and i suggested that she get over cause there was some road workers on the side and she like refused to do that and stayed in the the right lane so we argued a bit about that

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how would your best friend describe you

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: caring and enthusatic for life

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good have you ever served in the military

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: pretty easy i do not sleep as well as i did when i was younger but for the most part i i sleep well once in a while i will wake up you know at like four in the morning or five in the morning when i want to sleep notill seven and not be able to get back to sleep but in general it is pretty good

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are you like when you do not sleep well

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i feel tired and not as motivated as usual and then sometimes wanna take a nap you know in the afternoon

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay have you noticed any changes in your behavior or thoughts lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay what advice would you give yourself ten or twenty years ago

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: ten or twenty years ago i guess to i i wish i would have invested money or bought like a house or something when i was younger that would probably be the advice i would give myself

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good how close are you to your family

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: pretty close much closer than i was when i was younger and although i would say i am probably closer to friends and people that are in a spiritual counity with me than i am able to get to my family

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay what are some things that usually put you in a good mood

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: being outdoors in nature and exercising and also singing

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are you most proud of in your life

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: the fact that i have gone with followed my heart and did what i wanted to do versus gong with what i think i should do

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is great when was the last time you felt really happy

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i guess yesterday i was i spent the day by the beach and just bicycled and went skating and visited some old friends there

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: aw how did you feel in that moment

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: felt very relaxed and invigurated and i also felt like i miss living by the beach because i used to live really close to the beach
